## Style

- [x] Standardize typing constraints. (Pyright) *
- [ ] Enforce complexity constraints. (Lizard) -
- [x] Enforce utility gate constraints. (Vulture)
- [x] Enforce redundancy constraints. (jscpd) *
- [x] Plan and enforce initial architectural constraints. (Semgrep)
  - [ ] Expand the ruleset as the Python ↔ Ansible constitution hardens.
  - [ ] Enforce the rule that inventory topology stays complete and auditable: each host declared in `ansible/inventory/hosts.ini` must have a matching `ansible/inventory/host_vars/<host>.yml`, and orphaned `host_vars/*.yml` files must be rejected. (needs a test, not Semgrep)
  - [x] Enforce the rule that durable secrets live only in `ansible/group_vars/all/vault.yml`: app credentials, sudo passwords, and other long-lived secrets must not be stored in `host_vars`, extra vault files, or ad hoc inventory data.
- [ ] Ban generic dicts, object, and any types.

### Policy Coverage Backlog

- [ ] Every `ansible/apps/*` role must have a corresponding entry in `ansible/registry.yml`.
- [ ] Every `ansible/apps/*` role must have `backup/`, `restore/`, and `tasks/` directories.
- [ ] Every `ansible/apps/*` role must have coverage in `tests/test_ansible_apps.py` or `tests/e2e/`.
- [ ] `group_vars` and `host_vars` remain the only allowed Ansible variable sources; playbooks must not define variables directly.

